commit.message:
Remove emacsql-log-buffer accessor for good

Deprecating the `emacsql-log-buffer' accessor wasn't graceful to begin
with ([1: 3ec2c96], [2: f58cdd1]) and now (#119) we have learned that
it also causes issues.  Instead remove it outright and be done with it.

commit.message:
Use `put' instead of `setf' and `get'

Using `setf' together with a getter, is noisier than just using
the corresponding setter by itself.

However, stick to (setf (gethash ...)...)', because the argument
order of `puthash' is weird.

a regular variables means that one cannot immediately know that it
is not a generalized variable.

Handle missing module gracefully

If the module theoretically is the best backend, but we cannot
use it, then display a warning, instructing the user to install
the Elisp packages as well as the shared library.

Closes https://github.com/magit/forge/issues/552.
Closes https://github.com/magit/forge/issues/551.

commit.message:
Hard-require sqlite or sqlite3 once we know it is needed

That way, if the required feature isn't available, then we get an
error mentioning that, which is more meaningful than an error about
some function or variable not being defined.

Re https://github.com/magit/closql/issues/9.

commit.message:
Rename "process" slot to "handle" and make emacsql-process obsolete

This slot was named "process" when all connector classes used a
subprocess to communicate with their databases.  Using a process is
fragile, which is the reason why `emacsql-sqlite-builtin-connection'
and `emacsql-sqlite-module-connection' were created.

The slot was not renamed because it was only intended for internal use
anyway, and renaming it comes with the risk of breaking packages that
accessed it directly anyway.

But to avoid confusion, rename it to `handle' now.  Also document what
types its value may have and that it is only intended for internal
use.  Make the `emacsql-process' accessor function obsolete, and forgo
providing a renamed substitute, to avoid advertising direct access to
the slot.  For a limited time only, continue to allow direct access to
the internal slot under its obsolete name, but make noise about it.

Closes #112.
